[src:dart/language] Mixins are a way of reusing code in multiple class hierarchies.
[src:dart/language] To add a mixin's capabilities to a class, just extend the class with the mixin.
[src:dart/language] `PilotedCraft` now has the `astronauts` field as well as the `describeCrew()` method.
[src:dart/language] All classes implicitly define an interface.
[src:dart/language] Read more about implicit interfaces, or about the explicit `interface` keyword.
[src:dart/language] You can create an abstract class to be extended (or implemented) by a concrete class.
[src:dart/language] Abstract classes can contain abstract methods (with empty bodies).
[src:dart/language] Any class extending `Describable` has the `describeWithEmphasis()` method, which calls the extender's implementation of `describe()`.
